    "abstract": "Lattices used in cryptography are integer lattices. Defining and generating a \"random integer lattice\" are interesting topics. A generation algorithm for random integer lattice can be used to serve as a random input of all the lattice algorithms. In this paper, we recall the definition of random integer lattice given by G.Hu et al. and present an improved generation algorithm for it via Hermite Normal Form. It can be proved that with probability >= 0.99, this algorithm outputs an n-dim random integer lattice within O(n^2) operations.",
    "keywords": [
      "random integer lattice",
      "Hermite Normal Form",
      "generation algorithm"
    ],
    "category": "Public-key cryptography",
